TL;DR — PLAIN LANGUAGE SUMMARY (not legally binding)
=============================================================================

Before you read the full license, here is the gist in everyday language:

  SOFTWARE:
    You can use, copy, modify, and share this software for free. If you
    release your own standalone scraping tool based on it, keep it open
    source. If you just use it as a library inside a bigger project, you
    do not have to open-source your project. Give credit to the original
    authors either way.

  SCRAPED DATA:
    Scraping something does not make it yours. The people who created the
    content still own it. You are responsible for following the law and
    respecting content creators.

  AI / MACHINE LEARNING:
    Training a model on scraped data does not give you ownership of that
    data. Original creators keep their rights. Follow AI regulations.

  PROHIBITED USES:
    Do not use this software to harass, stalk, or surveil people. Do not
    resell scraping as a hosted service without adding real value. Do not
    scrape more data than you actually need.

  LIABILITY:
    The software is provided as-is. The authors are not responsible if
    something goes wrong, including legal trouble from how you use it.

  The full, legally binding text follows below.

=============================================================================
PART I — DEFINITIONS
=============================================================================

1. DEFINITIONS

   The following terms have precise meanings throughout this license:

   "Software" means the source code, object code, documentation,
   configuration files, build scripts, icons, stylesheets, and all other
   files distributed alongside this license text.

   "Derivative Work" means any work that is based on, incorporates, or
   modifies the Software in whole or in part.

   "Standalone Scraping Tool" means a software product whose primary
   purpose is web scraping, data collection, or automated content
   extraction from websites or web services.

   "Library Use" means incorporating portions of the Software as a
   component, module, or dependency within a larger software project
   whose primary purpose is NOT web scraping.

   "Scraped Content" means any data, text, images, audio, video,
   structured data, metadata, or other content collected, extracted,
   downloaded, or otherwise obtained using the Software.

   "Original Creator" means the person, organization, or entity that
   authored, published, or holds rights to content that may be scraped.

   "Scraping-as-a-Service" means offering a hosted or managed service
   whose primary value proposition is providing scraping, crawling, or
   data extraction capabilities to third parties, whether for a fee or
   for free, using this Software as the primary scraping engine.

   "Personal Data" means any information relating to an identified or
   identifiable natural person, as defined by applicable data protection
   laws including but not limited to the GDPR, CCPA, PIPL, and LGPD.

   "Data Minimization" means limiting the collection, processing, and
   retention of Scraped Content to what is strictly necessary for the
   stated, legitimate purpose of the scraping activity.

   >>> What this means in practice:
   >>> These definitions set the vocabulary for the rest of the license.
   >>> If a term is capitalized, it carries the specific meaning above.

