PART III — SCRAPED DATA: OWNERSHIP & RESPONSIBILITY
=============================================================================

5. NO OWNERSHIP OF SCRAPED CONTENT

   Neither the authors of this Software, its contributors, its users,
   nor any organization employing or contracting with the above, acquire
   any ownership, copyright, license, or intellectual property rights
   over Scraped Content by the mere act of scraping, collecting,
   downloading, caching, indexing, transforming, or storing it.

   To be unambiguously clear:

     a) Scraping content does NOT transfer ownership of that content.
     b) Scraping content does NOT create a new copyright over that
        content.
     c) Scraping content does NOT grant a license to use, reproduce,
        distribute, display, or create derivative works from that
        content.
     d) Aggregating, reformatting, cleaning, deduplicating, or otherwise
        processing Scraped Content does NOT create new intellectual
        property rights over the underlying content.
     e) Storing Scraped Content in a database, dataset, file, or any
        other format does NOT constitute authorship of that content.
     f) Making Scraped Content available through an API, website, or
        service does NOT transfer or create rights.
     g) Translating, summarizing, paraphrasing, or otherwise
        transforming Scraped Content does NOT extinguish the rights of
        Original Creators in the underlying work.

   >>> What this means in practice:
   >>> Just because you scraped it does not mean you own it. The original
   >>> creator's rights survive every transformation you apply.

6. ORIGINAL RIGHTS PRESERVED

   ALL rights in Scraped Content — including but not limited to
   copyright, trademark, trade secret, database rights, moral rights,
   publicity rights, privacy rights, sui generis database rights, and
   any other intellectual property or proprietary rights — belong to,
   and remain exclusively with, the Original Creators, authors,
   publishers, and/or rights holders.

   This applies without limitation to all types of content:

     - Text, articles, blog posts, comments, reviews, descriptions
     - Images, photographs, illustrations, graphics, icons, logos
     - Audio recordings, music, podcasts, sound effects
     - Video, animations, livestream recordings
     - Source code, compiled code, scripts, configuration files
     - Databases, datasets, spreadsheets, structured data
     - Trademarks, brand elements, trade dress, service marks
     - Personal Data, biographical information, contact details
     - Metadata, tags, categories, taxonomies
     - User-generated content, forum posts, social media content

=============================================================================
PART IV — ETHICAL USE, DATA MINIMIZATION & PROHIBITED CONDUCT
=============================================================================

7. ETHICAL SCRAPING GUIDELINES

   Users of this Software SHOULD adhere to the following ethical
   principles. While not all of these are strict legal requirements in
   every jurisdiction, they represent the standards this project expects
   of its community:

     a) RESPECT ROBOTS.TXT — Honor robots.txt directives and other
        machine-readable access controls where technically feasible.

     b) RATE LIMITING — Implement reasonable rate limits to avoid
        overloading target servers. Do not intentionally degrade the
        performance or availability of any website or service.

     c) IDENTIFY YOURSELF — Where practical, use a descriptive
        User-Agent string so site operators can contact you.

     d) HONOR OPT-OUT SIGNALS — Respect meta tags, HTTP headers, and
        other signals indicating that content should not be scraped
        or indexed.

     e) CITE SOURCES — When publishing or sharing Scraped Content,
        provide proper attribution to the Original Creator.

     f) MINIMIZE PERSONAL DATA — Avoid collecting Personal Data unless
        it is strictly necessary for a legitimate, stated purpose.

   >>> What this means in practice:
   >>> Be a good internet citizen. Do not hammer servers, respect
   >>> opt-outs, and always give credit.

8. DATA MINIMIZATION REQUIREMENTS

   Users of this Software MUST practice data minimization:

     a) COLLECT ONLY WHAT YOU NEED — Do not scrape entire websites or
        databases when only a subset of data is required for your
        stated purpose.

     b) RETENTION LIMITS — Do not retain Scraped Content longer than
        necessary for your stated purpose. Establish and follow a data
        retention schedule.

     c) SECURE STORAGE — Store Scraped Content using reasonable security
        measures appropriate to the sensitivity of the data.

     d) DELETION — Delete Scraped Content when it is no longer needed,
        when the Original Creator requests removal, or when required by
        applicable law.

     e) PERSONAL DATA — When scraping Personal Data, apply heightened
        data minimization standards consistent with applicable data
        protection laws.

   >>> What this means in practice:
   >>> If you only need product prices, do not also scrape user reviews,
   >>> profile photos, and email addresses. Collect the minimum, store
   >>> it securely, and delete it when you are done.

9. PROHIBITED USES

   The following uses of this Software are expressly PROHIBITED:

     a) HARASSMENT AND STALKING — Using the Software to collect
        information about individuals for the purpose of harassing,
        threatening, intimidating, doxxing, or stalking them.

     b) SURVEILLANCE — Using the Software to conduct mass surveillance
        of individuals, monitor political activities, track religious
        or ethnic affiliations, or build profiles for discriminatory
        purposes, except as required by applicable law and carried out
        by authorized governmental entities with proper legal authority.

     c) CIRCUMVENTION — Using the Software to circumvent technical
        protection measures, access controls, authentication
        mechanisms, or paywalls in violation of applicable law.

     d) DECEPTION — Using the Software to create fake accounts, generate
        spam, impersonate others, or engage in phishing or social
        engineering.

     e) WEAPONS AND HARM — Using the Software to collect information
        for the purpose of causing physical harm to individuals or
        groups, or for the development of weapons systems.

   Violation of this Section 9 constitutes a material breach of this
   license, automatically terminating all rights granted herein.

   >>> What this means in practice:
   >>> Do not use this software to hurt, spy on, or deceive people.
   >>> If you do, your license is immediately revoked.

10. ANTI-SCRAPING-AS-A-SERVICE

    You may NOT use this Software as the primary or core engine of a
    Scraping-as-a-Service offering without substantial additional value.

    Specifically:

      a) You may NOT simply wrap this Software in an API, web
         interface, or managed service and offer scraping capabilities
         to third parties as the primary product.

      b) You MAY use this Software as a component within a larger
         product or service that provides substantial additional
         functionality, analysis, transformation, or value beyond
         raw scraping — such as data analytics platforms, research
         tools, business intelligence services, or content monitoring
         solutions.

      c) You MAY offer consulting, integration, or development
         services that involve this Software.

      d) You MAY use this Software internally within your organization
         without restriction.

    The distinction is between reselling the Software's scraping
    capability as a thin wrapper (prohibited) and using the Software
    as one component of a genuinely differentiated product (permitted).

    >>> What this means in practice:
    >>> You cannot just put this scraper behind a pay-wall API and sell
    >>> "scraping as a service." But you can build a real product that
    >>> happens to use this scraper under the hood.

