PART V — AI AND MACHINE LEARNING
=============================================================================

11. AI/ML TRAINING AND SCRAPED CONTENT

    The following terms apply to the use of Scraped Content in
    connection with artificial intelligence and machine learning:

      a) TRAINING — Training AI or ML models on Scraped Content does
         NOT grant ownership of the training data to the model creator,
         trainer, deployer, or any downstream user.

      b) NO INHERITED RIGHTS — AI/ML models trained on Scraped Content
         do NOT inherit any rights to the content used for training.

      c) OUTPUTS — Outputs generated by AI/ML models trained on Scraped
         Content may be subject to the intellectual property rights of
         Original Creators if the outputs are substantially similar to,
         derived from, or reproduce the training data.

      d) COMPLIANCE — Users who train AI/ML models on Scraped Content
         are solely responsible for:
         (i)   Ensuring they have the legal right to use the content
               for training purposes.
         (ii)  Complying with applicable AI/ML regulations, including
               the EU AI Act, and any future legislation.
         (iii) Implementing and honoring opt-out mechanisms for content
               creators who do not wish their work to be used for
               AI/ML training.
         (iv)  Maintaining records of training data provenance where
               required by law.

      e) SOFTWARE AI COMPONENTS — The Software itself may include AI/ML
         capabilities (such as NuExtract integration). The software
         license terms (Part II) apply to the Software's AI components.
         The data ownership terms (Part III) apply to any content
         processed by those components.

      f) TRANSPARENCY — When distributing AI/ML models trained on
         Scraped Content obtained using this Software, users SHOULD
         disclose that web-scraped data was used in training, along
         with a general description of the data sources.

    >>> What this means in practice:
    >>> You can use scraped data to train AI models, but the original
    >>> creators still own their content. Follow AI regulations, honor
    >>> opt-outs, and be transparent about your training data.

