PART VI — INTERNATIONAL LAW AND USER RESPONSIBILITY
=============================================================================

12. USER RESPONSIBILITY

    Users of this Software are solely and exclusively responsible for:

      a) Ensuring they have the legal right to scrape, store, process,
         analyze, transform, and/or redistribute any content they
         collect.

      b) Complying with all applicable laws, regulations, and legal
         frameworks in every jurisdiction where they operate or where
         the target servers are located, including but not limited to:

         PRIVACY AND DATA PROTECTION:
           - General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR) — EU/EEA
           - California Consumer Privacy Act / California Privacy
             Rights Act (CCPA/CPRA) — United States (California)
           - Personal Information Protection Law (PIPL) — China
           - Lei Geral de Protecao de Dados (LGPD) — Brazil
           - Protection of Personal Information Act (POPIA) —
             South Africa
           - Personal Data Protection Act (PDPA) — Singapore,
             Thailand, and others
           - Privacy Act — Australia, Canada, New Zealand
           - Act on the Protection of Personal Information (APPI) —
             Japan
           - Other national and regional data protection laws

         INTELLECTUAL PROPERTY:
           - Copyright and intellectual property laws
           - Digital Millennium Copyright Act (DMCA) — United States
           - EU Copyright Directive (including Article 4 text and
             data mining provisions)
           - Database rights and sui generis database protections
           - Trademark and trade secret laws

         COMPUTER ACCESS AND FRAUD:
           - Computer Fraud and Abuse Act (CFAA) — United States
           - Computer Misuse Act — United Kingdom
           - Equivalent computer access and fraud laws in other
             jurisdictions

         AI-SPECIFIC REGULATIONS:
           - EU AI Act
           - Other current and future AI-specific regulations

         OTHER:
           - Applicable terms of service of scraped websites
           - Applicable industry-specific regulations (e.g., HIPAA,
             FERPA, GLBA)

      c) Conducting data protection impact assessments where required
         by applicable law before scraping Personal Data at scale.

      d) Implementing appropriate consent mechanisms where required
         by applicable law, including obtaining valid legal bases for
         processing Personal Data under the GDPR (consent, legitimate
         interest, etc.).

      e) Honoring data subject rights, including rights of access,
         rectification, erasure, restriction, portability, and
         objection, as provided by applicable data protection laws.

      f) Implementing appropriate data retention and deletion policies
         consistent with Section 8 (Data Minimization Requirements).

      g) Properly attributing and citing original sources when using
         or publishing Scraped Content.

      h) Honoring takedown requests, opt-out signals, and removal
         requests from rights holders in a timely manner.

    >>> What this means in practice:
    >>> YOU are responsible for following the law — not the software
    >>> authors. Laws vary by country; know the rules that apply to
    >>> you and to the servers you are scraping.

13. CONSENT AND LEGAL BASIS

    Where applicable law requires consent or another legal basis for
    the collection and processing of data:

      a) Users MUST obtain and document the required consent or
         legal basis BEFORE using the Software to collect such data.

      b) The existence of this Software or this license does NOT
         constitute consent from any website, service, or individual
         to be scraped.

      c) Users MUST NOT rely on this license as a legal basis for
         processing Personal Data under the GDPR or any other data
         protection framework.

    >>> What this means in practice:
    >>> This license gives you permission to use the software. It does
    >>> NOT give you permission to scrape any particular website or
    >>> collect any particular person's data.

