PART VIII — CITATIONS
=============================================================================

15. CITATIONS

    Auto-generated citations (MLA 9th edition, APA 7th edition, and
    other formats) are provided as a convenience to assist users with
    proper attribution. However:

      a) Citations are generated algorithmically and may contain errors,
         omissions, or inaccuracies.

      b) Citations MUST be verified by the user before use in academic
         work, publications, legal proceedings, journalism, or any
         context where accuracy is required.

      c) Providing a citation does NOT constitute legal permission to
         use the cited content. Users must independently verify their
         right to use any cited material.

      d) Citation generation is a feature of the Software, not a legal
         service. No attorney-client relationship is created.

      e) The citation format and metadata are derived from Scraped
         Content and are subject to the same data ownership terms in
         Part III — the underlying cited works belong to their
         Original Creators.

    >>> What this means in practice:
    >>> The software can generate citations for you, but always
    >>> double-check them. A citation is not permission to use content.

